Boil a large #pot of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for your pasta. Slice open the
sausage casing of the @Pork & Oregano Sausage{1}, peel them off and discard them.

Chop the head off the @Purple Sprouting Broccoli{1} and cut it in half lengthways.
Chop the remaining stalk into bite-sized pieces.

Boil the broccoli for about ~{90%seconds}. Keeping the water, lift the broccoli
out and keep to the side.

> Keep the water on high heat for the pasta.

Cook the @Wheat Penne Pasta{180%g} for around ~{10%mins} or until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a slight hint of
> firmness left in the middle.

Heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot add the
pork and break up with a #wooden spoon. Once the pork has lost its raw colour
add the drained broccoli.

After a couple of mins add a few tbsp of the water from your pasta. Add the
@Green Pesto{3%tbsp} and stir everything together.

Add the drained pasta into the #pan. Grate your @Parmesan Cheese{2%tbsp}, scatter
over half of it and toss everything together. Serve with the remaining parmesan
and a few grinds of @ground black pepper{}.